{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2a6cb1b1-8a2f-4a9d-82e0-a9abdba9169e","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options:**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# API with Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg\n\n# API with Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer token auth without Azure AD, use `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific auth option?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b8575f74-9dc1-4998-8193-a4557aec9706","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/web development question. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge without needing to search the filesystem, since there's nothing in the current working directory that would be relevant.","outputTokens":291,"requestId":"93CF:162674:A190DF:BAD30B:69F2A769"},"id":"ccd4db28-28ed-4941-8ca2-38fe96fc0e50","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:50:58.512Z","parentId":"2e4e8760-5b34-472d-bcb7-8175df000113"}
